HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 277
BY REPRESENTATIVE BUTLER
A RESOLUTION
To commend Jeffery Craig Whittington for his outstanding coaching career.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Jeffery Craig Whittington for his legacy
as a mentor and leader of high school athletes and to commend him on his outstanding
coaching career; and
WHEREAS, Coach Whittington began coaching at Bayou Chicot High School in
1989 and enjoyed a thirty-seven-year career at six schools; his love of sports and the
outdoors guided his leadership approach, and he used athletics as a platform to teach
responsibility, resilience, teamwork, and character; and
WHEREAS, Coach Whittington consistently elevated high school basketball
programs throughout his career; he led four different schools to the Louisiana High School
Athletic Association (LHSAA) State Tournament Final Four and won a district
championship at every school where he coached; and
WHEREAS, Coach Whittington led Holy Savior Menard to its first-ever appearance
in the state finals and a state runner-up finish, and he led Sacred Heart School to its first
semifinals appearance; he led Pine Prairie High School to the school's only district
championship since its 2005 consolidation; and
WHEREAS, Coach Whittington won four state titles as a head coach; during his
tenure at University Academy of Central Louisiana, he claimed back-to-back championships
in the Mid-South Association of Independent Schools (MAIS) in 2015 and 2016 and back-
to-back LHSAA championships in 2020 and 2021; he won a state championship as an
assistant coach at Glenmora High School in 2005; and
WHEREAS, Coach Whittington has received numerous awards for his impressive
coaching successes; he earned thirteen District Coach of the Year awards, eight All-Parish
