coaching honors, an All-Cenla Coach of the Year Award, and the 2015 MAIS All-State
Coach of the Year Award; in 2021, he was selected as an assistant coach for the East All-
Star Team; and
WHEREAS, Coach Whittington has cemented his place among the most
accomplished coaches in Louisiana high school basketball history; over the course of his
LHSAA coaching career, he recorded seven hundred thirty-three wins, including six hundred
thirty-eight wins coaching girls basketball and ninety-five wins coaching boys basketball;
he totaled one hundred seventy-five wins coaching in the MAIS; and
WHEREAS, Coach Whittington coached future NCAA Division I, NAIA, and
NJCAA athletes; he guided players who earned All-Star recognition and mentored future
LHSAA coaches who carry on his legacy of leadership; and
WHEREAS, in addition to basketball, Coach Whittington coached softball and
earned nine district championships, numerous deep playoff runs, and coach of the year
honors; his success across different sports highlights his lifelong dedication to athletic
development; and
WHEREAS, Coach Whittington's family are the central focus of his life; he and his
wife, April, have shared more than thirty-four years of marriage and are the proud parents
of three daughters and grandparents of three grandsons; he anchors his work on the values
of family, faith, and community; and
WHEREAS, Jeffery Craig Whittington is an outstanding leader whose many
successes highlight his dedication to coaching and the mentorship of high school athletes;
he is deserving of recognition for his incredible achievements.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Jeffery Craig Whittington for his
outstanding coaching career; does hereby express enduring appreciation for his mentorship
of high school athletes in Louisiana; and does hereby extend sincere wishes that he continue
to prosper in all of his endeavors.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
